NAME
    gcloud alpha scheduler jobs create-app-engine-job - create a Cloud
        Scheduler job with an App Engine target

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha scheduler jobs create-app-engine-job JOB --schedule=SCHEDULE
        [--description=DESCRIPTION] [--header=HEADER]
        [--http-method=HTTP_METHOD; default="post"]
        [--max-attempts=MAX_ATTEMPTS] [--max-backoff=MAX_BACKOFF; default="1h"]
        [--max-doublings=MAX_DOUBLINGS; default=16]
        [--max-retry-duration=MAX_RETRY_DURATION]
        [--min-backoff=MIN_BACKOFF; default="5s"]
        [--relative-url=RELATIVE_URL; default="/"] [--service=SERVICE]
        [--time-zone=TIME_ZONE; default="Etc/UTC"] [--version=VERSION]
        [--message-body=MESSAGE_BODY
          | --message-body-from-file=MESSAGE_BODY_FROM_FILE]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Create a Cloud Scheduler job with an App Engine target.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Job resource - The job to create. This represents a Cloud resource. (NOTE)
     Some attributes are not given arguments in this group but can be set in
     other ways. To set the [project] attribute: provide the flag [job] on the
     command line with a fully specified name; provide the flag [--project] on
     the command line; set the property [core/project]. To set the [location]
     attribute: provide the flag [job] on the command line with a fully
     specified name; as the location of the current project's App Engine App.
     This must be specified.

       JOB
          The ID of the job or a fully qualified identifier for the job.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --schedule=SCHEDULE
        String, English-like description of the schedule at which the job
        should be run. See
        https://cloud.google.com/appengine/docs/standard/python/config/cronref#schedule_format
        for details.

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     --description=DESCRIPTION
        A human-readable description of the job.

     --header=HEADER
        "KEY: VALUE" pair, HTTP header to include in the request. May be
        repeated. Example: --header 'Accept-Language: en-us' --header 'Accept:
        text/plain'

     --http-method=HTTP_METHOD; default="post"
        HTTP method to use for the request. HTTP_METHOD must be one of: delete,
        get, head, post, put.

     --max-attempts=MAX_ATTEMPTS
        Int, the number of times to retry the request if it fails or times out.
        Must be in range 0-5 inclusive.

     --max-backoff=MAX_BACKOFF; default="1h"
        Duration, the maximum amount of time to wait before retrying a task
        after it fails. Ex. 10s (default is 1h).

     --max-doublings=MAX_DOUBLINGS; default=16
        Int, the maximum number of times that the interval between failed job
        retries will be doubled before the increase becomes constant.

     --max-retry-duration=MAX_RETRY_DURATION
        The time limit for retrying a failed task, measured from when the task
        was first run. If specified with --max-attempts, the task will be
        retried until both limits are reached. Default is 0 (which means
        unlimited)

     --min-backoff=MIN_BACKOFF; default="5s"
        Duration, the minimum amount of time to wait before retrying a task
        after it fails. Ex. 10s (default is 5s).

     --relative-url=RELATIVE_URL; default="/"
        String, relative URL to use for the request (beginning with "/").

     --service=SERVICE
        String, ID of the App Engine service to which to send the request.

     --time-zone=TIME_ZONE; default="Etc/UTC"
        String, a time zone name from the tz database
        (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tz_database).

     --version=VERSION
        String, ID of the App Engine version to which to send the request.

     At most one of these may be specified:

       --message-body=MESSAGE_BODY
          String, a data payload to be included as the body of the HTTP
          request. May only be given with compatible HTTP methods (PUT or
          POST).

       --message-body-from-file=MESSAGE_BODY_FROM_FILE
          String, a data payload to be included as the body of the HTTP
          request. May only be given with compatible HTTP methods (PUT or
          POST).

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

API REFERENCE
    This command uses the cloudscheduler/v1alpha1 API. The full documentation
    for this API can be found at: https://cloud.google.com/cloud-scheduler/

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. Usually,
    users of ALPHA commands and flags need to apply for access, agree to
    applicable terms, and have their projects whitelisted. Contact Google or
    sign up on a product's page for ALPHA access. Product pages can be found at
    https://cloud.google.com/products/.

